   },
   "source": [
    "### Data Loading (Batching)\n",
    "\n",
    "Training data is loaded in mini-batches to enable GPU-based training. Each batch consists of images and corresponding target vectors, with preprocessing and augmentation applied each batch.\n",
    "\n",
    "Shuffling is used during training to prevent ordering effects and improve generalization."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {
    "id": "XSP4ZnmPA3SF"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "resnet_train_batches = create_batches(train_df, img_dir, resnet_train_transform, batch_size, target_cols, True)\n",
    "resnet_val_batches = create_batches(val_df, img_dir, resnet_val_transform, batch_size, target_cols, True)\n",
    "\n",
    "levit_train_batches = create_batches(train_df, img_dir, levit_train_transform, batch_size, target_cols, True)\n",
    "levit_val_batches = create_batches(val_df, img_dir, levit_val_transform, batch_size, target_cols, True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "0tD3RLDRugp3"
   },
   "source": [
    "### Modeling\n",
    "\n",
    "A simple baseline is defined by predicting the mean of each target variable from the training data. Convolutional neural networks (ResNet-18 and LeViT-128s) are then trained to learn image-based representations and improve upon this baseline. These architectures allow comparison between standard and more efficient transformer-based vision models, given our setup.\n",
    "\n",
    "The task is optimized using mean squared error (MSE), consistent with the multi-label regression setting. Training uses AdamW with cosine annealing to support stable convergence."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 61,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
    },
    "id": "0T94K6bImNq3",
    "outputId": "b0cdde4a-83eb-4012-9981-6936951f6dc4"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Baseline RMSE: 0.16466134786605835\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "mean_values = train_df[target_cols].mean().values\n",
    "mean_target = torch.tensor(mean_values, dtype=torch.float32)\n",
    "\n",
    "baseline_score = baseline_rmse(val_df, mean_target, target_cols)\n",
    "print(f\"Baseline RMSE: {baseline_score}\")"
   ]
